I asked if I could pay for them and have them mailed or held for will call, or any other options?  Same answer. "No."  I was told that I need to come to the store to buy the gift card. The kale that came with my chicken tinga bowl noticeably detracted from the rest of the meal, tasting like store brand greens that had been left out for significantly too long before being served.  I feel bad leaving such a harsh rating since the service was fine and the other components of the salad were solid, but again I think that a restaurant that markets itself as providing gourmet, locally sourced fresh ingredients shouldn't be serving vegetables that are one step above a fast food salad.  Overall not recommended.

This place is usually packed during lunch time, so it's best to come before 11:30am if you want to get your salad as quickly as possible. I loved getting their Smoky Santa Cruz all the time, and it was the only salad I would order; unfortunately, they decided to change the menu and took it off for good. They can still make a variation of it, but they don't have the same kale they used for the specific salad. Since I got tired of having to point out which ingredients I wanted instead of just telling them Smoky Santa Cruz, I decided to try the Chicken Tinga.  The Chicken Tinga is served warm, and they do not chop it up because it would get pretty messy if they tried to chop it. It's good with the Mexican Goddess dressing, and I like it when they use a lot of it on my salad. Overall, the salad is good on a chilly day, but I wish they would bring back the Smoky Santa Cruz.

I come here pretty frequently and haven't had any complaints before but had an abysmal experience today. Ordered ahead as I usually do for my order to come at 12:15. Didn't get it until 12:45. The area near the register was PACKED with people waiting for online orders with no communication from staff saying they were  having issues, no emails saying it might be late, etc. Just about 40 frustrated people (all with 12:15 orders) waiting in a tight area. Then, the employee who was bringing them out didn't even announce them as she brought them in, forcing people to squeeze by each other just to see if theirs had been placed. Just totally unorganized chaos. Really disappointed. I also had gotten two on one order with a friend, and the employee put the larger bags on the side without saying anything. I had a hunch it may have been mine, so I had to squeeze through people just to see if it was mine. Thankfully it was, but the whole experience was very frustrating. I usually order for pickup at 11:45; I guess I'll stick to that. I don't know if it it was staffing issues or not, but I hope they fix this issue.
